@@@ 3113 Pretrig Tracks
This field is only useful if Streak Mode is On.  If the 
value entered is greater than zero, the detector will 
REQUIRE a signal at the Trig In connector in order to run.
When acquisition is started, the detector will wait for the
trigger signal to go HIGH.  At this time, it will begin 
shifting lines from the exposed area into the masked area.
When the trigger signal goes LOW, the detector will continue
to shift as before, but it will count the number of tracks
(exposed regions) shifted.  When the number of tracks equal
to (#Tracks - Pretrig Tracks) has been shifted, the detector
will close the shutter and complete the acquisition by reading
the tracks from the masked area.  The effect of this will be
that the masked area will contain data from after the time the
trigger signal went low, plus Pretrig Tracks amount of data 
from before the trigger signal went low.  The amount of time
represented by the Pretrig Tracks is displayed on this menu.
